Docs.typeparam: The type of the elements to be stored in the collection.
Docs.summary: Represents a thread-safe, unordered collection of objects.

remarks.format:
## Remarks Bags are useful for storing objects when ordering doesn't matter, and unlike sets, bags support duplicates. <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentBag%601> is a thread-safe bag implementation, optimized for scenarios where the same thread will be both producing and consuming data stored in the bag.
<xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentBag%601> accepts `null` as a valid value for reference types.
For more information, see the entry [FAQ: Are all of the new concurrent collections lock-free?](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/pfxteam/faq-are-all-of-the-new-concurrent-collections-lock-free/) in the Parallel Programming with .NET blog.
## Examples The following example shows how to add and remove items from a <xref:System.Collections.Concurrent.ConcurrentBag%601>:
